<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Computer Hardware Overview</h1>
        
        <h2>CPU (Central Processing Unit)</h2>
        <p>The brain of the computer, responsible for executing instructions and calculations.</p>
        
        <h2>GPU (Graphics Processing Unit)</h2>
        <p>Handles graphics rendering, essential for gaming and video editing.</p>
        
        <h2>Memory</h2>
        <p>Stores active data for quick access, enabling multitasking and smooth performance.</p>
        
        <h2>Storage</h2>
        <p>Holds files, applications, and the OS, providing long-term data storage.</p>
        
        <h2>Motherboard</h2>
        <p>Connects and enables communication between all hardware components.</p>
        
        <h2>Power Supply</h2>
        <p>Provides electricity to ensure all components function correctly.</p>
        
        <h2>Case</h2>
        <p>Houses and protects components while providing cooling and ventilation.</p>
    </div>
